WEBVTT

1
00:00:21.310 --> 00:00:22.620
Out!

2
00:00:23.880 --> 00:00:24.960
Lucky!

3
00:00:24.960 --> 00:00:28.420
Karasuno                            Aoba Johsai

4
00:00:25.240 --> 00:00:28.420
We won the first set against Seijoh!

5
00:00:28.420 --> 00:00:30.360
We won the first set!

6
00:00:30.360 --> 00:00:31.820
All right!

7
00:00:31.820 --> 00:00:33.880
Take the second set, too!

8
00:00:34.500 --> 00:00:35.790
Sorry.

9
00:00:35.790 --> 00:00:39.550
That idiot! Not only was that 
obviously Kindaichi's ball,

10
00:00:39.550 --> 00:00:41.350
but then he steals it only to hit it out?!

11
00:00:41.690 --> 00:00:44.700
And they were at set point!

12
00:00:44.700 --> 00:00:46.350
How can I even start to explain?!

13
00:00:47.270 --> 00:00:49.320
That's dangerous!

14
00:00:50.150 --> 00:00:51.450
Iwaizumi!

15
00:00:51.450 --> 00:00:55.050
Yeah, that's it! That's how to start!

16
00:00:55.050 --> 00:00:56.570
Oh, I'm fine...

17
00:00:57.250 --> 00:01:00.920
I was feeling stressed because
 I hadn't been put in the match.

18
00:01:00.920 --> 00:01:03.040
That's not a valid reason!

19
00:01:03.040 --> 00:01:04.670
Who is that?

20
00:01:04.670 --> 00:01:08.000
Why would Seijoh swap in a guy like that?

21
00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:10.800
Aoba Johsai                                Karasuno

22
00:01:13.000 --> 00:01:15.610
Ah, that guy from earlier is there.

23
00:01:15.610 --> 00:01:17.420
He's starting this set.

24
00:01:17.800 --> 00:01:22.090
Since he's replacing Kunimi, 
he might be pretty smart.

25
00:01:22.090 --> 00:01:23.140
Be careful.

26
00:01:23.140 --> 00:01:25.840
You're more or less free 
to play how you want,

27
00:01:25.840 --> 00:01:28.230
but if you interfere with us, 
you'll be back on the bench.

28
00:01:29.590 --> 00:01:32.540
Just don't do any unnecessarily dangerous plays.

29
00:01:32.540 --> 00:01:33.210
Right.

30
00:01:33.210 --> 00:01:35.610
Why did you only reply to Iwa-chan?!

31
00:01:35.610 --> 00:01:39.720
He challenged Iwaizumi-san 
a whole bunch of times,

32
00:01:39.720 --> 00:01:44.410
and lost every single time, so he 
at least listens to Iwaizumi-san.

33
00:01:44.410 --> 00:01:45.820
Not happening!

34
00:01:44.410 --> 00:01:46.580
What are we, a wolf pack?

35
00:01:46.860 --> 00:01:50.710
Well, the one who'll be 
using him is Oikawa-san.

36
00:01:50.710 --> 00:01:52.040
Right.

37
00:01:52.410 --> 00:01:54.840
We're gonna take this 
momentum and run with it!

38
00:01:54.840 --> 00:01:56.730
We're gonna win the second set, too!

39
00:01:56.730 --> 00:01:58.090
Yeah!

40
00:02:13.900 --> 00:02:20.410
Haikyu!!

41
00:03:29.060 --> 00:03:31.440
Episode 21: "The Destroyer"

42
00:03:32.180 --> 00:03:34.900
Asahi-san, get one! Nice serve!

43
00:03:39.180 --> 00:03:40.020
Out!

44
00:03:41.150 --> 00:03:43.290
! Sorry!

45
00:03:43.290 --> 00:03:44.810
So close! You'll get the next one!

46
00:03:44.810 --> 00:03:45.610
Don't mind!

47
00:03:45.610 --> 00:03:46.350
Your face is scary!

48
00:03:46.350 --> 00:03:47.620
What'd you say?!

49
00:03:47.620 --> 00:03:49.240
Oikawa, nice serve!

50
00:03:47.620 --> 00:03:50.330
Aoba Johsai                                Karasuno

51
00:03:51.820 --> 00:03:52.950
Out, out!

52
00:03:55.060 --> 00:03:56.190
Sorry!

53
00:03:56.190 --> 00:03:57.960
Don't mind. We'll get the next one.

54
00:03:57.960 --> 00:04:00.120
I wonder what's wrong with Oikawa-kun.

55
00:04:00.120 --> 00:04:01.680
He messed up another serve.

56
00:04:01.680 --> 00:04:03.680
But that speed is incredible.

57
00:04:03.680 --> 00:04:05.930
Touching that would break off your arms.

58
00:04:07.140 --> 00:04:09.990
I feel like we're getting more in sync.

59
00:04:12.960 --> 00:04:14.490
Tsukishima, nice serve!

60
00:04:17.430 --> 00:04:18.400
you!

61
00:04:18.400 --> 00:04:20.040
Nice cover, Iwa-chan!

62
00:04:19.180 --> 00:04:21.820
There are three attackers on the 
front line... Who's it going to be?

63
00:04:21.820 --> 00:04:23.110
Mad Dog-chan.

64
00:04:23.390 --> 00:04:25.030
Open from the right?!

65
00:04:25.430 --> 00:04:26.970
What the heck is "Mad Dog"?!

66
00:04:26.970 --> 00:04:29.200
Is it an alias? That's awesome!

67
00:04:30.450 --> 00:04:31.960
One blocker!

68
00:04:30.760 --> 00:04:32.410
What?

69
00:04:33.300 --> 00:04:35.510
He's sprinting basically parallel to the net?

70
00:04:36.380 --> 00:04:37.540
Three blockers!

71
00:04:46.310 --> 00:04:48.220
That cut shot was insane!

72
00:04:49.180 --> 00:04:50.860
So that's why he was running like that.

73
00:04:50.860 --> 00:04:51.850
Hm?

74
00:04:52.240 --> 00:04:54.570
When you're facing the block,

75
00:04:54.570 --> 00:04:56.460
there are choices you can make,

76
00:04:56.460 --> 00:04:58.980
but chances are you'll get blocked.

77
00:05:00.530 --> 00:05:05.230
Instead, he hit it to cut across the blockers.

78
00:05:05.230 --> 00:05:07.550
He comes in from the right 
and hits with his right hand,

79
00:05:07.550 --> 00:05:09.610
pulling off that incredible cut shot.

80
00:05:10.870 --> 00:05:12.980
Mad Dog is amazing!

81
00:05:14.580 --> 00:05:17.790
Aoba Johsai                                Karasuno

82
00:05:15.640 --> 00:05:17.380
Iwaizumi, nice serve!

83
00:05:20.920 --> 00:05:22.960
It's coming back! Chance ball!

84
00:05:22.960 --> 00:05:24.010
! Sorry!

85
00:05:24.620 --> 00:05:29.130
Oikawa and Iwaizumi can really pressure 
us if they make a lot of serves.

86
00:05:25.890 --> 00:05:26.820
Got it!

87
00:05:29.130 --> 00:05:31.470
And now, there's also the Mad Dog...

88
00:05:33.680 --> 00:05:34.890
A double quick?!

89
00:05:40.690 --> 00:05:41.730
All right!

90
00:05:42.120 --> 00:05:47.310
Great, great, Kentaro! Push it, 
push it, Kentaro! One more time!

91
00:05:42.400 --> 00:05:46.160
I know he's a mad dog, but 
he's not going to keep biting,

92
00:05:46.160 --> 00:05:48.120
so you can come in.

93
00:05:48.770 --> 00:05:52.010
The Shrimp knew you weren't 
going to hit it, Kindaichi.

94
00:05:52.420 --> 00:05:54.730
Sorry, I was a bit scared.

95
00:05:55.200 --> 00:05:57.160
Iwa-chan, one more! Nice serve!

96
00:06:02.320 --> 00:06:03.130
Yeah!

97
00:06:03.130 --> 00:06:04.800
Nice receive!

98
00:06:05.280 --> 00:06:06.260
C quick!

99
00:06:11.700 --> 00:06:13.400
Y-You okay?!

100
00:06:13.400 --> 00:06:16.390
Y-Yeah, I'm fine. I'm fine.

101
00:06:16.390 --> 00:06:20.020
It's that #16 again! Three points in a row!

102
00:06:21.840 --> 00:06:26.480
Even though they're getting in, 
those attacks seem pretty violent.

103
00:06:26.480 --> 00:06:30.280
Ever since that #16 came in,
 their attack rhythm has changed.

104
00:06:30.760 --> 00:06:32.360
Kyotani, nice kill!

105
00:06:32.990 --> 00:06:35.030
Iwaizumi, one more! Nice serve!

106
00:06:32.990 --> 00:06:35.950
Aoba Johsai                          Karasuno

107
00:06:38.790 --> 00:06:39.920
Sorry!

108
00:06:40.220 --> 00:06:41.700
All right!

109
00:06:40.520 --> 00:06:42.380
We finally get a point back.

110
00:06:47.270 --> 00:06:48.130
Nice, Makki!

111
00:06:50.520 --> 00:06:51.340
Here it comes!

112
00:06:51.340 --> 00:06:52.780
Let's battle, Mad Dog!

113
00:06:55.700 --> 00:06:58.180
After letting #16 go all out on his attacks,

114
00:06:59.120 --> 00:07:00.760
now it's a slide hit from Kindaichi!

115
00:07:02.900 --> 00:07:04.360
All right!

116
00:07:07.550 --> 00:07:10.890
He's angry that he was used as a decoy.

117
00:07:10.890 --> 00:07:15.780
Though that itself makes him
 an even better decoy.

118
00:07:16.640 --> 00:07:20.350
I'll make your fangs even sharper.

119
00:07:21.590 --> 00:07:26.210
Let's play carefully! That's a 
Seijoh we're not familiar with.

120
00:07:26.210 --> 00:07:28.670
Aoba Johsai                                               Karasuno

121
00:07:26.790 --> 00:07:28.230
Kindaichi, nice serve!

122
00:07:30.380 --> 00:07:31.350
Got it!

123
00:07:32.160 --> 00:07:33.510
Left!

124
00:07:32.160 --> 00:07:33.510
Center!

125
00:07:35.300 --> 00:07:38.780
Is this a strategy where one middle 
blocker is always on Hinata?

126
00:07:38.780 --> 00:07:39.890
It's up! Cover!

127
00:07:39.890 --> 00:07:41.480
Got it! Kyotani, get the last!

128
00:07:41.960 --> 00:07:43.190
Sorry! It's close to the net!

129
00:07:43.680 --> 00:07:44.900
Three blockers!

130
00:07:44.900 --> 00:07:46.180
If he hits it, it'll get caught.

131
00:07:46.640 --> 00:07:47.570
Bring it back once!

132
00:07:51.950 --> 00:07:54.280
Nice block!

133
00:07:52.400 --> 00:07:53.790
All right!

134
00:07:54.820 --> 00:07:58.030
That was an intense full swing.

135
00:07:58.030 --> 00:07:59.150
That idiot...

136
00:07:59.150 --> 00:08:02.750
You idiot! There are other 
ways to hit or even feint!

137
00:08:03.080 --> 00:08:06.710
If I don't attack in with all I've got,
 it doesn't feel good!

138
00:08:10.150 --> 00:08:11.040
Why you...

139
00:08:11.040 --> 00:08:12.900
Now, now, Mizoguchi-kun...

140
00:08:13.410 --> 00:08:16.420
He'll eventually correct 
what he has to correct.

141
00:08:16.960 --> 00:08:17.850
Right...

142
00:08:18.340 --> 00:08:20.810
So about him being pretty smart...

143
00:08:20.810 --> 00:08:22.920
I just thought that he might be!

144
00:08:22.920 --> 00:08:26.560
He doesn't know the bliss of 
 a feint... What a waste.

145
00:08:26.560 --> 00:08:29.020
Aoba Johsai                                  Karasuno

146
00:08:28.180 --> 00:08:29.020
Makki!

147
00:08:30.840 --> 00:08:32.200
Nice, Nishinoya!

148
00:08:36.050 --> 00:08:38.200
Nice, Makki! Mad Dog-chan!

149
00:08:39.290 --> 00:08:41.500
It's the guy who hits from the side again.

150
00:08:41.500 --> 00:08:43.130
I'm going to stop him this time!

151
00:08:46.960 --> 00:08:48.750
All right!

152
00:08:48.750 --> 00:08:50.330
We're saved.

153
00:08:50.330 --> 00:08:54.860
Having three blockers on 
you and then trying to hit

154
00:08:54.860 --> 00:08:57.470
as hard as you can on a narrow 
course is pretty risky.

155
00:08:57.960 --> 00:09:01.480
That attack that seems to be
 powerful, but unreliable...

156
00:09:01.480 --> 00:09:04.560
Since he didn't start in this match,

157
00:09:04.960 --> 00:09:08.180
that #16 just might be a double-edged sword.

158
00:09:08.940 --> 00:09:10.820
That #16's spike...

159
00:09:11.610 --> 00:09:13.900
It's all shwing! Whoosh!

160
00:09:13.900 --> 00:09:14.860
It's so cool!

161
00:09:15.640 --> 00:09:17.410
Right? Right?

162
00:09:18.450 --> 00:09:22.010
Of course, Mad Dog-chan is a strong jumper,

163
00:09:22.010 --> 00:09:24.120
as well as unbelievable dorsal 
and abdominal muscles...

164
00:09:25.920 --> 00:09:29.930
He goes in tight and lets loose!

165
00:09:31.160 --> 00:09:32.720
It's intense, right?

166
00:09:32.720 --> 00:09:35.470
If he gets through a block, 
the ball won't be easy to pick up.

167
00:09:36.050 --> 00:09:38.200
He finally got one in.

168
00:09:38.200 --> 00:09:40.380
Oikawa used him well.

169
00:09:40.380 --> 00:09:43.420
If it were me, I would have 
passed to someone else.

170
00:09:43.420 --> 00:09:45.850
All right!

171
00:09:43.420 --> 00:09:46.220
Tenacity and boldness.

172
00:09:46.980 --> 00:09:51.320
You can't use the mad dog if you're scared.

173
00:09:49.350 --> 00:09:50.820
Kyotani, nice serve!

174
00:09:54.150 --> 00:09:55.210
Out!

175
00:09:57.280 --> 00:09:58.600
All right!

176
00:09:57.340 --> 00:10:00.160
His serve is quite dynamic, too.

177
00:09:58.880 --> 00:09:59.820
Nice call!

178
00:10:00.160 --> 00:10:02.870
Aoba Johsai                                Karasuno

179
00:10:00.920 --> 00:10:02.870
One step forward, one step back.

180
00:10:02.870 --> 00:10:04.620
It's basically a stalemate.

181
00:10:04.620 --> 00:10:09.330
Yeah. That #16 can score a lot, 
but makes just as many mistakes.

182
00:10:07.880 --> 00:10:09.330
All right!

183
00:10:11.880 --> 00:10:13.660
Iwaizumi-san, nice serve!

184
00:10:24.470 --> 00:10:25.770
Cover! Cover!

185
00:10:24.910 --> 00:10:25.770
Makki, get the last!

186
00:10:27.640 --> 00:10:28.330
Got it!

187
00:10:28.330 --> 00:10:29.350
One more! One more!

188
00:10:31.560 --> 00:10:32.770
The receive is off!

189
00:10:33.540 --> 00:10:34.480
It's coming to the left!

190
00:10:34.930 --> 00:10:36.320
It's on purpose.

191
00:10:38.360 --> 00:10:40.660
Mad Dog! His timing's even faster now.

192
00:10:41.050 --> 00:10:42.370
Second tempo!

193
00:10:43.170 --> 00:10:45.900
We're well aware that he's 
a double-edged sword.

194
00:10:45.900 --> 00:10:47.830
That's why we put him in!

195
00:10:52.000 --> 00:10:53.710
All right!

196
00:10:52.000 --> 00:10:53.710
All right!

197
00:10:52.920 --> 00:10:58.720
Great, great, Kentaro! Push it, 
push it, Kentaro! One more time!

198
00:10:54.180 --> 00:10:56.140
That's a crazy angle.

199
00:10:56.140 --> 00:10:58.590
Tearing off a block with your own hands

200
00:10:58.590 --> 00:11:00.930
is definitely bliss only a setter knows.

201
00:11:03.390 --> 00:11:05.630
Get on it!

202
00:11:05.630 --> 00:11:06.600
Nice receive!

203
00:11:06.600 --> 00:11:08.310
Center!

204
00:11:12.440 --> 00:11:14.900
Aoba Johsai                 Karasuno

205
00:11:12.970 --> 00:11:14.900
All right!

206
00:11:15.400 --> 00:11:16.980
Shoyo, nice serve!

207
00:11:16.980 --> 00:11:19.000
Hinata, give it all you've got!

208
00:11:17.340 --> 00:11:20.460
Again, I'm rotated to the back 
without getting a single spike in...

209
00:11:25.870 --> 00:11:26.900
Got it!

210
00:11:31.160 --> 00:11:32.460
Nice receive!

211
00:11:33.400 --> 00:11:35.260
All right! Here we go!

212
00:11:41.770 --> 00:11:43.680
Hinata's back attack!

213
00:11:43.680 --> 00:11:45.890
My first back attack!

214
00:11:48.440 --> 00:11:49.560
All right!

215
00:11:51.350 --> 00:11:54.020
Did you think now was your 
opportunity to use that?

216
00:11:55.190 --> 00:11:56.730
I did, too.

217
00:11:57.310 --> 00:12:01.580
Keep calm, keep calm, keep calm...

218
00:11:59.500 --> 00:12:02.700
My back attack debut...

219
00:12:03.070 --> 00:12:05.480
I thought they could break it, too.

220
00:12:05.480 --> 00:12:08.120
If they don't start catching up,
 this'll get ugly.

221
00:12:08.520 --> 00:12:09.130
Ah!

222
00:12:09.920 --> 00:12:10.580
Ah?!

223
00:12:10.580 --> 00:12:12.870
Sugawara got called to the bench?

224
00:12:13.880 --> 00:12:16.000
They're changing setters again?

225
00:12:16.000 --> 00:12:18.770
Kageyama doesn't seem to be doing bad.

226
00:12:18.770 --> 00:12:21.030
What happened now was just due 
to Oikawa being intense...

227
00:12:21.940 --> 00:12:26.050
Actually, I don't think they're 
switching out Kageyama.

228
00:12:26.380 --> 00:12:28.510
We're not going to let you just take it.

229
00:12:28.920 --> 00:12:30.760
We're going to do everything we can.

230
00:12:33.020 --> 00:12:39.980
Haikyu!!

231
00:12:40.030 --> 00:12:46.990
Haikyu!!

232
00:12:48.210 --> 00:12:51.450
Is Sugawara-san switching with someone?

233
00:12:51.850 --> 00:12:54.060
It's a strategic player trade.

234
00:12:54.060 --> 00:12:56.160
Don't make it sound so complicated.

235
00:12:56.160 --> 00:12:57.830
Come on, college student.

236
00:12:58.370 --> 00:13:01.770
When someone's not doing 
well or someone gets hurt,

237
00:13:01.770 --> 00:13:05.430
there are times where a pinch server 
or a one-point blocker goes in, right?

238
00:13:06.310 --> 00:13:08.890
The latter is a strategic player trade.

239
00:13:11.810 --> 00:13:13.150
All right!

240
00:13:11.810 --> 00:13:14.270
Aoba Johsai                                Karasuno

241
00:13:13.150 --> 00:13:14.270
Iwaizumi, nice kill!

242
00:13:14.680 --> 00:13:16.970
In the last Seijoh match,

243
00:13:16.970 --> 00:13:20.880
they were cornered and ended up 
being forced to switch, but...

244
00:13:21.640 --> 00:13:25.510
This time, it's most likely 
for them to get the win.

245
00:13:26.820 --> 00:13:30.970
#16 is an unknown element, and dealing 
with Seijoh has gotten even more difficult.

246
00:13:31.540 --> 00:13:34.480
But we're not going to just 
let them take the game.

247
00:13:34.480 --> 00:13:36.920
Yes, but before that...

248
00:13:38.260 --> 00:13:39.920
Oikawa-san, nice serve!

249
00:13:47.170 --> 00:13:48.680
Oh, here it comes.

250
00:13:50.160 --> 00:13:52.250
That's a nice serve toss.

251
00:14:02.190 --> 00:14:04.110
All right!

252
00:14:04.110 --> 00:14:07.320
It's like getting slapped 
in the face really hard

253
00:14:07.800 --> 00:14:10.390
and coming back to reality.

254
00:14:11.640 --> 00:14:17.750
Neither of us can let the other win, 
and we've both trained to win.

255
00:14:18.200 --> 00:14:20.040
It all makes sense.

256
00:14:20.760 --> 00:14:24.780
It's to be expected, but the reality 
is still so terrifying.

257
00:14:25.760 --> 00:14:27.470
Aoba Johsai                                Karasuno

258
00:14:27.810 --> 00:14:29.340
One more, nice serve!

259
00:14:37.560 --> 00:14:38.520
Front!

260
00:14:39.940 --> 00:14:41.900
! I held back too much!

261
00:14:40.240 --> 00:14:41.900
Nice receive, Nishinoya!

262
00:14:41.900 --> 00:14:42.830
Left!

263
00:14:42.830 --> 00:14:43.360
Tanaka-san!

264
00:14:43.810 --> 00:14:44.820
Three blockers!

265
00:14:49.950 --> 00:14:51.660
All right!

266
00:14:51.660 --> 00:14:53.770
Ryu! Well done!

267
00:14:55.080 --> 00:14:56.120
Ah, here it comes.

268
00:14:56.400 --> 00:14:57.430
The switch.

269
00:14:59.080 --> 00:15:01.320
All right! We're gonna catch up.

270
00:15:01.320 --> 00:15:02.540
Yeah!

271
00:15:03.520 --> 00:15:06.000
Suga, we need that nice serve!

272
00:15:06.000 --> 00:15:06.800
Yup.

273
00:15:07.510 --> 00:15:08.760
Bring it!

274
00:15:08.760 --> 00:15:09.970
Suga-san, nice serve!

275
00:15:11.990 --> 00:15:14.920
Serving right after switching in 
sure is nerve wracking.

276
00:15:15.800 --> 00:15:18.890
But there's only one place to aim for.

277
00:15:21.250 --> 00:15:21.850
Kyotani!

278
00:15:23.060 --> 00:15:23.940
That was good!

279
00:15:24.390 --> 00:15:27.980
Now their #16 was late in attacking.

280
00:15:35.740 --> 00:15:37.950
All right!

281
00:15:37.950 --> 00:15:39.110
A break!

282
00:15:37.950 --> 00:15:39.910
Aoba Johsai                               Karasuno

283
00:15:40.690 --> 00:15:42.940
Suga-san! One more, nice serve!

284
00:15:47.650 --> 00:15:48.250
Again...

285
00:15:49.010 --> 00:15:51.200
Kyotani is a wing spiker,

286
00:15:51.200 --> 00:15:53.860
but he's the type who goes after 
quicks one after another.

287
00:15:53.860 --> 00:15:58.140
They're getting Kyotani to move on the 
serves so he can't go after the spikes.

288
00:15:58.490 --> 00:16:01.530
Karasuno's #2 has hit on an annoying tactic.

289
00:16:04.410 --> 00:16:05.900
Daichi-san, nice receive!

290
00:16:05.900 --> 00:16:07.110
All right!

291
00:16:07.110 --> 00:16:08.120
Yes!

292
00:16:10.890 --> 00:16:12.900
Kageyama pulled back from an attack?

293
00:16:12.900 --> 00:16:15.370
Five Karasuno spikers?!

294
00:16:21.160 --> 00:16:23.120
All right!

295
00:16:23.120 --> 00:16:25.100
N-Nice kill...

296
00:16:25.100 --> 00:16:28.340
it. Kageyama's straight is awesome!

297
00:16:29.520 --> 00:16:31.990
Is this what you call two setters?

298
00:16:33.130 --> 00:16:35.330
Even more jargon...

299
00:16:35.330 --> 00:16:36.180
Then...

300
00:16:36.880 --> 00:16:40.140
Strategic one point two setters!

301
00:16:40.140 --> 00:16:41.360
Right?

302
00:16:41.360 --> 00:16:42.350
That's too long.

303
00:16:42.600 --> 00:16:44.860
All right! One more point!

304
00:16:43.350 --> 00:16:45.270
Aoba Johsai            Karasuno

305
00:16:46.590 --> 00:16:48.080
All right!

306
00:16:48.080 --> 00:16:50.190
Switching players now?

307
00:16:50.460 --> 00:16:51.980
They're in a good spot.

308
00:16:52.920 --> 00:16:56.400
All of the third-years are good at receiving.

309
00:16:56.400 --> 00:16:57.530
I see...

310
00:16:58.120 --> 00:17:10.340
Net

311
00:16:58.120 --> 00:17:10.340
Server

312
00:16:58.410 --> 00:17:02.730
Volleyball has a rotation system, and 
the players' positions are always changing.

313
00:17:03.280 --> 00:17:08.790
The front line and backline have different jobs,
 so each rotation has a specialty.

314
00:17:09.600 --> 00:17:11.190
And apparently...

315
00:17:10.340 --> 00:17:22.560
Net

316
00:17:10.340 --> 00:17:22.560
Server

317
00:17:11.800 --> 00:17:14.000
The rotation when Tsukishima is serving,

318
00:17:14.000 --> 00:17:16.570
is weak for both defense and offense.

319
00:17:17.170 --> 00:17:20.140
There are only two spikers in front,

320
00:17:20.140 --> 00:17:22.580
and Tsukishima can't block from the back.

321
00:17:24.160 --> 00:17:26.410
Considering their rotation,

322
00:17:26.410 --> 00:17:30.630
it's quite a feat that they were 
able to keep getting points.

323
00:17:31.230 --> 00:17:33.940
Aoba Johsai

324
00:17:32.240 --> 00:17:33.940
Well, what's it going to be?

325
00:17:34.220 --> 00:17:36.300
How about we make them miss?

326
00:17:36.300 --> 00:17:37.160
Yeah.

327
00:17:41.250 --> 00:17:43.580
Suga-san! One more! Nice serve!

328
00:17:45.120 --> 00:17:47.080
They're going after Kyotani again!

329
00:17:48.040 --> 00:17:49.060
Got it!

330
00:17:49.750 --> 00:17:51.160
Nice, Makki!

331
00:17:51.160 --> 00:17:53.460
As usual, they figure thinks out quickly.

332
00:17:56.950 --> 00:17:58.090
All right!

333
00:18:03.310 --> 00:18:04.760
Suga-san, nice!

334
00:18:04.760 --> 00:18:05.590
Thanks.

335
00:18:06.050 --> 00:18:09.400
it. I wanted to take it to a tie.

336
00:18:09.400 --> 00:18:11.980
Aoba Johsai                     Karasuno

337
00:18:12.880 --> 00:18:13.690
Tanaka-san!

338
00:18:16.550 --> 00:18:17.650
Yeah!

339
00:18:18.450 --> 00:18:19.990
Kageyama, nice serve!

340
00:18:22.350 --> 00:18:23.160
Iwa-chan!

341
00:18:31.330 --> 00:18:32.460
He picked it up!

342
00:18:32.460 --> 00:18:33.670
Watacchi!

343
00:18:34.990 --> 00:18:35.840
Right!

344
00:18:39.800 --> 00:18:41.130
All right!

345
00:18:41.130 --> 00:18:42.330
How do I put this?

346
00:18:42.920 --> 00:18:47.980
They're forcing #16 to do all their attacks.

347
00:18:47.980 --> 00:18:49.480
Yeah.

348
00:18:50.160 --> 00:18:52.560
Maybe they're trying to get 
all the attention on #16

349
00:18:52.560 --> 00:18:54.940
and then hand it off to someone else.

350
00:18:55.280 --> 00:18:57.930
No matter how many balls go to the Mad Dog,

351
00:18:57.930 --> 00:18:59.900
I'm not gonna be tricked anymore!

352
00:19:01.330 --> 00:19:01.950
Tanaka-san!

353
00:19:01.950 --> 00:19:03.030
Got it!

354
00:19:06.200 --> 00:19:07.740
Nice, Makki!

355
00:19:07.740 --> 00:19:10.620
I know why we put Kyotani in...

356
00:19:11.060 --> 00:19:14.280
It's for a little extra punch power.

357
00:19:14.280 --> 00:19:15.880
For a bit more offense.

358
00:19:16.740 --> 00:19:18.010
Mad Dog-chan!

359
00:19:19.020 --> 00:19:21.820
If we don't use him to his 
fullest, we're in trouble!

360
00:19:23.920 --> 00:19:25.520
All right!

361
00:19:25.520 --> 00:19:26.680
it...

362
00:19:29.850 --> 00:19:32.170
Here they come, here they come!

363
00:19:33.510 --> 00:19:35.320
Hey, we're in a good spot.

364
00:19:35.320 --> 00:19:38.660
They managed to get into the 20's.

365
00:19:38.660 --> 00:19:42.750
Even if they lose this set, 
Karasuno won the first set.

366
00:19:42.750 --> 00:19:45.280
As long as they get the 
next one, they'll be fine.

367
00:19:45.280 --> 00:19:46.010
No...

368
00:19:46.780 --> 00:19:49.910
They need to do whatever 
they can to win this set.

369
00:19:47.410 --> 00:19:49.110
We're gonna finish this!

370
00:19:50.250 --> 00:19:52.630
If they don't, I have a 
bad feeling about the outcome.

371
00:19:54.870 --> 00:19:57.240
Kidaichi! One more! Nice serve!

372
00:19:57.880 --> 00:19:58.780
Front!

373
00:20:00.360 --> 00:20:01.960
S-Sorry!

374
00:20:01.960 --> 00:20:03.340
You're thinking about your aim too much.

375
00:20:05.050 --> 00:20:05.870
Here we go!

376
00:20:05.870 --> 00:20:07.150
Tanaka, nice serve!

377
00:20:08.970 --> 00:20:10.430
Nice receive!

378
00:20:21.640 --> 00:20:23.240
All right!

379
00:20:23.610 --> 00:20:28.200
Trying not to think about something 
is the same as thinking about it.

380
00:20:28.200 --> 00:20:30.410
Aoba Johsai                                            Karasuno

381
00:20:28.720 --> 00:20:30.410
Kyotani, nice serve!

382
00:20:34.990 --> 00:20:36.670
Bring it!

383
00:20:48.640 --> 00:20:50.480
All right!

384
00:20:50.480 --> 00:20:51.960
The double-edged sword...

385
00:20:53.030 --> 00:20:58.120
Putting in #16 was sink-or-swim 
bet for Seijoh,

386
00:20:58.120 --> 00:21:02.420
but I thought they had
 already used him successfully.

387
00:21:03.030 --> 00:21:04.030
Sensei!

388
00:21:04.030 --> 00:21:04.790
Yes!

389
00:21:06.000 --> 00:21:06.640
All right!

390
00:21:06.640 --> 00:21:08.220
Again? So quick!

391
00:21:08.220 --> 00:21:10.580
Now Karasuno's used up 
all of their time outs.

392
00:21:12.790 --> 00:21:15.260
With #16 as their new weapon,

393
00:21:15.790 --> 00:21:18.040
they were able to score 
point after point in the chaos,

394
00:21:18.300 --> 00:21:22.710
and use #16's abilities to the 
fullest during most of this set.

395
00:21:24.000 --> 00:21:27.970
Kyotani is a slow-starter 
who requires a lot of support.

396
00:21:28.310 --> 00:21:30.010
But, once he gets started, he's strong.

397
00:21:31.110 --> 00:21:32.520
This isn't good.

398
00:21:32.520 --> 00:21:36.220
When a new set starts, it tends to mimic

399
00:21:36.220 --> 00:21:39.190
the end of the previous set, 
and the match as a whole.

400
00:21:39.810 --> 00:21:43.150
At this rate, Seijoh definitely 
has the upper hand.

401
00:21:40.120 --> 00:21:43.720
Let's bring it in! Karasuno, fight!

402
00:21:43.150 --> 00:21:45.840
Do whatever you can to just 
take this set and win it!

403
00:21:43.720 --> 00:21:45.840
Yeah!

404
00:21:49.730 --> 00:21:52.080
Kyotani, one more! Nice serve!

405
00:21:55.040 --> 00:21:56.730
Let's get this one!

406
00:21:56.730 --> 00:21:58.150
Yeah!

407
00:22:00.680 --> 00:22:03.250
Oh, shut up already. I know.

408
00:22:13.010 --> 00:22:14.790
Please let me go in.

409
00:23:46.680 --> 00:23:48.990
Your engine's starting to get 
warmed up, Mad Dog-chan.

410
00:23:48.990 --> 00:23:50.320
Let's finish this!

411
00:23:50.320 --> 00:23:52.700
Kyotani, we're gonna take this set.

412
00:23:52.700 --> 00:23:53.310
Right.

413
00:23:53.310 --> 00:23:55.200
Why do you only answer Iwa-chan?!

414
00:23:55.200 --> 00:23:57.080
I'm not gonna give you any more tosses!

415
00:23:57.080 --> 00:24:00.300
Next time on Haikyu!!:
"The Former Coward's Fight."

416
00:23:57.160 --> 00:24:01.000
Episode 22: "The Former Coward's Fight"
